altText: Chart: Propagandists lost no time putting their own spin on events after raids and skirmishes. In American newspapers, the enemy was painted
detailedDescription: Propagandists lost no time putting their own spin on events after raids and skirmishes. In American newspapers, the enemy was painted as a bloodthirsty and ruthless foe committing atrocities on the defenseless civilians. The British reports characterized their raids as harmless.
